    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T19:00:00-05:00" n="791"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./8–1944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 2, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2555. You may inform Massigli in reply to his notes of June 6 and August 16 [<hi
                        rend="italic">14</hi>], 1944, reference your airgram A–178 of June 16, your
                    despatch 351 of June 16, your telegram 2693 of August 16 and your despatch 483
                    of August 19,<note n="33" xml:id="d791fn33">Despatches 351 and 483 not
                        printed.</note> that this Government is of opinion that the issuance of a
                    new governmental declaration regarding German war crimes would not be profitable
                    at this time and might well be inadvisable. You may add that the position of the
                    Allied Governments, including the Moscow Declaration, has been explicitly stated
                    and widely and repeatedly published and that position will continue to be
                    referred to in propaganda and otherwise as opportunity offers. It is believed
                    that the French Committee will understand that our reluctance to follow the
                    procedure suggested results not from any waning interest but solely from
                    considerations of policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
